  Appendix 3  9 
C.  Copy Editor and Desktop Publishing Specialist 

4.  Under the direct supervision of the assistant chief economist of ERMF, and in consultation 
with the ADO production coordinator, the copy editor will (i) edit ADO 2005 and ADO 2005 Update 
in accordance with ADB’s editorial style; (ii) be responsible for typesetting and proofreading the 
text, tables, and charts of the publication from the preliminary draft to the final copy and filming the 
output before forwarding to the external printer; (iii) be responsible for data linking to ensure data 
integrity and consistency in the final manuscript; and (iv) be responsible for converting the desktop 
file into pdf and html files for uploading on the ADB website. The copy editor must have full 
working knowledge of MSOffice (MSWord and MSExcel), Adobe Pagemaker/InDesign, and Corel 
Draw/Illustrator. 

5.  In particular, the copy editor cum desktop publishing specialist will 

(i)  edit ADO in conformity with ADB’s editorial style and usage; 
(ii)  edit ADO for consistency and accuracy; 
(iii)  edit the publication summary of ADO; 
(iv)  supervise the encoding of corrections as well as incorporation of tables, charts,  
and boxes; 
(v)  edit ADO for balance (in terms of layout); 
(vi)  review the final manuscript for filming; 
(vii)  prepare the definition, glossary of terms, and list of references; 
(viii)  edit all dissemination materials including press releases, speeches, questions  
and answers, key messages, and presentation slides;  
(ix)  convert desktop files to pdf and html formats; and 
(x)  perform  all  other  functions  and  responsibilities  as  may  be  assigned  by  the 
assistant chief economist of ERMF.
